\details{
An R6 class that manages a collection of CohortDef objects and maintains
metadata in a SQLite database.

The CohortManifest class manages multiple cohort definitions and stores their
metadata in a SQLite database located at inputs/cohorts/cohortManifest.sqlite.
Each CohortDef is assigned a sequential ID based on its position in the manifest.

This is the detection phase of the ATLAS maintenance workflow. Use this to identify
which ATLAS cohorts have changed, then optionally call \code{updateAtlasCohorts()} to
apply updates. Changes are detected by comparing expression JSON hashes.

This method updates ATLAS cohorts that have changed in the remote repository. It:
\itemize{
\item Fetches current definitions from ATLAS
\item Updates JSON files on disk
\item Recomputes and stores hashes
\item Updates the manifest database
}

Use \code{checkAtlasChanges()} first to identify which cohorts have changed, then call this method
to apply updates.

Requires that executionSettings has been set and includes:
\itemize{
\item A database connection (via getConnection()
\item workDatabaseSchema for the target schema
\item cohortTable with the desired table name
\item tempEmulationSchema if needed for the database platform
}

Requires that executionSettings has been set and includes:
\itemize{
\item A database connection (via getConnection()
\item workDatabaseSchema for the target schema
\item cohortTable with the desired table name
}

Requires that \code{executionSettings} has been set with a valid database connection,
\code{workDatabaseSchema}, and \code{cohortTable}.

Execution flow:
\enumerate{
\item Build dependency graph from all CohortDef objects
\item Validate no circular dependencies (error if found)
\item Topologically sort cohorts by dependencies (parents before children)
\item For each cohort in topological order:
\itemize{
\item circe cohorts: check SQL hash (existing logic)
\item dependent cohorts: compute dependency hash from parent hashes + rule
}
\item Render and execute SQL (circe uses SqlRender parameters, dependent uses metadata JSON)
\item Record checksums and dependency hashes in database
\item Report results with cohort_type, depends_on, dependency_status columns
}

Requires that executionSettings has been set and includes:
\itemize{
\item A database connection (via getConnection()
\item cdmDatabaseSchema (where the OMOP CDM data resides)
\item workDatabaseSchema (where cohort results are written)
\item cohortTable (destination table name)
\item tempEmulationSchema if needed for the database platform
}
}
